Text: Yes, that is the one, Annerose...
Now, move that floorboard!
A little song and dance, leading lady?
Wha—?!

Don't be silly... This is called practicing my
performance. I'm not singing, or dancing.

So it wasn't the "Shadow Power" I've heard so much
about, hm... What's this, your script or something?
Yes. Lady Beta wrote it.

Um...apparently she heard from Lady Gamma about
the encounter with Annerose the other day,

so she made a set of sample responses so there won't
be any chance of me messing up in getting Annerose
to do what she needs to do.
Wow, very smart of her. Mind if I take a look?
Be my guest. I was going to take a break anyway.
Don't mind if I do—

...There's also some one-liners meant for political
satire cartoons in the Midgar Newspaper.

Yeah. I'm guessing the intent is to use the media
to back Sergey into a corner in the arena of public
opinion as well.
What's wrong? Did you find something?

Heehee... So everything you do as a ghost is going
to be depicted in its entirety as a newspaper comic.
...WHAT?!

Which means...you will be truly dead and gone here
in the empire.
The past has no hold on me.

As a member of the Garden, I'll take center stage.
I'll become the ghost of Velgalta.
...So you've put it all behind you?

Yeah...I don't know. Can't say for sure yet,
but I do feel calm, refreshed, and—
How goes it, No. 111, No. 122?
Greetings, Lady Zeta.
Do you have an additional mission for us?
...You got a sec? I need to talk about something.
Yes, ma'am.
As you wish.
So...I actually want to lure out the Templars.

I was hoping to sync the day we execute our plan
with their movements. Think we can manage that?
*gasp*
But...!

I say that in full knowledge that it'll lower our
chances of success.

But if we know they're coming for certain, I want to
make this an opportunity to strike a blow to their
strength they won't forget... You get me, right?
Lady Zeta...!

With all due respect, Lady Zeta, I must ask...do you
have Lady Alpha's approval for this plan?
Hey, No. 122—
Heh...

All I can say is...she's the one who sent me as
backup, thinking we might cross paths with them.

In other words, you want the arrival of the Templars,
a potential showstopper, to be a deciding factor in
the flow of the operation?!

You in? Or maybe you'd rather tattle on my reckless
plan to Alpha?
W-Well...

So long as neither Sergey himself nor the Children
turn up, No. 111 and Annerose should be able to
handle the Cult on their own.

And it's reasonable to take a moderate, manageable
risk by purposely engineering the situation
ourselves in order ensure we avoid a presumably
greater risk.
...Ah, so you've changed your mind.

As long as no possessed lives get caught up in the
plot, there is next to no benefit in the Cult
locking horns with the Templars.

In short, another way of steering the Templars away
from Sergey or the Children would be to drag them
into this right from the very beginning, yes?
Precisely.
Not a bad idea. Can I use it?

Of course. And if by chance the plan should fail,
please say that it was me who talked you into it.

Hey, I'd never stoop that low. I'm always prepared
to take responsibility for my own actions.
So, we good to go on this, No. 111?
...As you wish.

Thanks. I'll let you know when I decide to
execute our plan.
Understood!
Yes, ma'am...!
...Hey, No. 122, why did you—

Lady Zeta is one to fixate on her own battles,
much as you once did.

And also as it was in your case, this fixation can
lead to unforeseen trouble when we least suspect it.
I...can't deny the truth of that...

Lady Zeta has offered to assist us, well aware that
her obsessions will be a hinderance.

Thus incorporating this obsession into the plan from
outset will allow us to adapt more easily to any
surprises that may arise.
Don't you agree?
Grr... You...have a point.

...At any rate, all I can do is prove I can do what
needs to be done!
